"{\"uid\": \"snopes.com-fact-check-imane-khelif-wbo\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"About this rating  On May 30, 2025, World Boxing, a different sanctioning body from the World Boxing Organization, announced that Khelif would not be allowed to compete in its events until passing a genetic sex-screening test.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 226, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 42, \"end\": 48, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5570277273345473e-15, \"text\": \"Boxing\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\"}, {\"begin\": 88, \"end\": 113, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Boxing_Organization\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"World Boxing Organization\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Boxing_Organization\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Boxing_Organization\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2023, hours before her gold medal bout in the Women's World Boxing Championships, the International Boxing Association (IBA) governing bodyalleged without proofthat Algerian boxer Imane Khelif did not meet the necessary requirements to compete as a woman.\", \"from\": 228, \"to\": 486, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 291, \"end\": 297, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5570277273345473e-15, \"text\": \"Boxing\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\"}, {\"begin\": 351, \"end\": 354, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9999978354754382, \"rank\": 2.164529101743221e-06, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}, {\"begin\": 396, \"end\": 404, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"score\": 0.91933109327737, \"rank\": 0.08771635866504816, \"text\": \"Algerian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\"}, {\"begin\": 411, \"end\": 423, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"score\": 0.9999996421621021, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Imane Khelif\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A year later, Khelifwon a gold medal at the Summer Olympics.\", \"from\": 488, \"to\": 548, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Anti-transgender activists including author J.K. Rowling and right-wing politicians like U.S. President Donald Trump drew attention to Khelif's victory and alleged that she was a man.\", \"from\": 549, \"to\": 732, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 593, \"end\": 597, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._K._Rowling\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.5257779652386805e-19, \"text\": \"J.K.\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._K._Rowling\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/J._K._Rowling\"}, {\"begin\": 653, \"end\": 665, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 8.014321895379676e-13, \"text\": \"Donald Trump\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Snopespreviously published a detailed story debunking the rumor.\", \"from\": 733, \"to\": 797, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Separately inMarchandMay2025, however, posts appeared online alleging that theWorld Boxing Organization (WBO), a different sanctioning body, had banned Khelif from competing in its events for life and stripped her of prize money and of her medals because she's a man.\", \"from\": 799, \"to\": 1066, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 883, \"end\": 889, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5570277273345473e-15, \"text\": \"Boxing\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The claim was false - World Boxing Organization PresidentGustavo Olivieri told Snopes via email that the WBO was not responsible for sanctioning amateur boxing (also called Olympic-style boxing) fights.\", \"from\": 1070, \"to\": 1272, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1149, \"end\": 1155, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snopes\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Snopes\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snopes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snopes\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He said the WBO only sanctioned professional boxing matches.\", \"from\": 1273, \"to\": 1333, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1285, \"end\": 1288, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Boxing_Organization\", \"score\": 0.9995328928631171, \"rank\": 0.00046732542815036487, \"text\": \"WBO\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Boxing_Organization\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Boxing_Organization\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Accordingly, any claims suggesting that the WBO has imposed a ban on amateur boxers are patently false,\\\" Olivieri wrote.\", \"from\": 1335, \"to\": 1456, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1380, \"end\": 1383, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Boxing_Organization\", \"score\": 0.9995328928631171, \"rank\": 0.00046732542815036487, \"text\": \"WBO\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Boxing_Organization\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Boxing_Organization\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The WBO does not oversee amateur boxing, nor does it have the authority to regulate or restrict the participation of amateur athletes in non-professional competitions.\\\"\", \"from\": 1457, \"to\": 1626, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1462, \"end\": 1465, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Boxing_Organization\", \"score\": 0.9995328928631171, \"rank\": 0.00046732542815036487, \"text\": \"WBO\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Boxing_Organization\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Boxing_Organization\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The response echoed anOctober 2024 news releasefrom the WBO, which said the organization \\\"had not tested, nor had it banned female boxer Imane Khelif.\\\"\", \"from\": 1628, \"to\": 1779, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1684, \"end\": 1687, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Boxing_Organization\", \"score\": 0.9995328928631171, \"rank\": 0.00046732542815036487, \"text\": \"WBO\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Boxing_Organization\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Boxing_Organization\"}, {\"begin\": 1765, \"end\": 1777, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"score\": 0.9999996421621021, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Imane Khelif\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There aresignificant rules differencesbetween professional and amateur boxing, including the fact that professional bouts have a purse.Sports Illustrated reported in October 2024that Khelif only has one professional fight to her name, a 2023 bout in Singapore that she won.\", \"from\": 1781, \"to\": 2054, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2031, \"end\": 2040, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Capital_punishment_in_Singapore\", \"score\": 0.9459770904140191, \"rank\": 0.05710804479797649, \"text\": \"Singapore\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Capital_punishment_in_Singapore\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Capital_punishment_in_Singapore\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"OnMay 30, 2025, World Boxing, a separate governing body set up by the International Olympic Committee (IOC) to replace the IBA (there werestrong concerns about corruption in the organization), announced that it would require all competitors to undergogenetic sex screeningbefore competing, specifically mentioning Khelif in its statement.\", \"from\": 2056, \"to\": 2394, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2078, \"end\": 2084, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5570277273345473e-15, \"text\": \"Boxing\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\"}, {\"begin\": 2126, \"end\": 2163, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 2179, \"end\": 2182, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9999978354754382, \"rank\": 2.164529101743221e-06, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Boxer Imane Khelif Makes Major Decision Just Months after Olympic Gender Row.\\\"\", \"from\": 2396, \"to\": 2475, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Independent, 23 Oct. 2024, https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/bo